Here is an example of JUnit 5 test cases for the `getConnection` method in the `AlarmReceiver` class:

```java
import org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeEach;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;
import org.mockito.Mock;
import org.mockito.MockitoAnnotations;

import static org.mockito.Mockito.*;

public class AlarmReceiverTest {

    @Mock
    private VMBParams vmbParams;

    @Mock
    private AlarmPostGreService alarmPostGreService;

    @Mock
    private PostingService alarmPointLookupService;

    private AlarmReceiver alarmReceiver;

    @BeforeEach
    public void setup() {
        MockitoAnnotations.initMocks(this);
        alarmReceiver = new AlarmReceiver(vmbParams, alarmPostGreService, alarmPointLookupService);
    }

    @Test
    public void testGetConnection_ConsumerNotNull() {
        VMBConfig vmbConfig = new VMBConfig();
        vmbConfig.setTopic("testTopic");
        // Set other properties of vmbConfig

        when(vmbParams.getConsumerVMBConfig()).thenReturn(vmbConfig);
        when(VMBUtil.createConsumerConnection(eq(vmbConfig), isNull())).thenReturn(mock(Consumer.class));

        alarmReceiver.getConnection();

        verify(vmbParams).getConsumerVMBConfig();
        verify(VMBUtil).createConsumerConnection(eq(vmbConfig), isNull());
        // Add other verification statements
    }

    @Test
    public void testGetConnection_ConsumerNull() {
        VMBConfig vmbConfig = new VMBConfig();
        vmbConfig.setTopic("testTopic");
        // Set other properties of vmbConfig

        when(vmbParams.getConsumerVMBConfig()).thenReturn(vmbConfig);
        when(VMBUtil.createConsumerConnection(eq(vmbConfig), isNull())).thenReturn(null);

        alarmReceiver.getConnection();

        verify(vmbParams).getConsumerVMBConfig();
        verify(VMBUtil).createConsumerConnection(eq(vmbConfig), isNull());
        verify(alarmReceiver, never()).shutdown();

        // Add other verification statements
    }

    // Add more test cases for other scenarios

}
```

In this example, we are using Mockito to mock the dependencies (`VMBParams`, `AlarmPostGreService`, `PostingService`) and the utility class `VMBUtil`. We initialize the `AlarmReceiver` object in the `setup` method using the mocks, and then we write individual test cases for different scenarios of the `getConnection` method. Within each test case, we mock the necessary method calls and verify the expected behavior using the `verify` statements.